    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nI noticed some nvim-treesitter injections stopped working, so I'm creating this issue.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n`luafile minimal.lua`\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\n\r\nvim.bo[buf].filetype = \"lua\"\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf, 0, -1, true, { \"---@type string\" })\r\n\r\nlocal root = vim.treesitter.get_parser(buf, \"lua\"):parse(true)[1]:root()\r\nlocal query = vim.treesitter.query.parse(\"lua\", [[\r\n(comment\r\n  content: (_) @injection.content\r\n  (#lua-match? @injection.content \"^%-%s*@\")\r\n  (#set! injection.language \"luadoc\")\r\n  (#offset! @injection.content 0 1 0 0))\r\n]])\r\n\r\nfor pattern, match, metadata in query:iter_matches(root, buf, nil, nil, { all = true }) do\r\n  vim.print({match[pattern][1]:range()})\r\n  vim.print(vim.treesitter.get_node_text(match[pattern][1], buf, { metadata = metadata }))\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI expect the range to be `{ 0, 3, 0, 15 }` (offset by one because of the predicate), and the node text to be `@type string`. Instead, the text is `-@type string`, indicating that offset is not applied\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.10.0 commit cc15ba212c7992c3f3aae8b90962862572b21e83\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nlinux 6.7.5-arch1-1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.32.1\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from source",
